The paper deals with the problem of preprocessing a convex polytope into a data structure to efficiently determine whether a query point is inside the polytope. This problem is related to computational geometry (cs.CG) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses approximation algorithms and techniques, which are relevant to numerical analysis (cs.NA) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper presents results on query time and space complexity, which are important topics in complexity theory (cs.CC).
